org.sbml.jsbml.math.compiler

Class ASTNode2Value<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.math.compiler.ASTNode2Value<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - 

    public class ASTNode2Value<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    When interpreting ASTNode2s, the ASTNode2Compiler takes elements of this class as arguments and performs its operations on it. Hence, this class represents the union of all possible types to which an abstract syntax tree can be evaluated, i.e., Boolean, CallableSBase, Number, or String. This class does not define what to do with these values or how to perform any operations on it. It is just the container of a value. The type of this value tells the ASTNode2Compiler which operation was performed to obtain the value stored in this object.

    1.0

        private ASTNode2Compiler compiler
        An ASTNode2Compiler that is needed in the case that this ASTNode2Value contains a derivative of CallableSBase as value to translate this value into a double. If the compiler does not convert instances of CallableSBase to double numbers, a ClassCastException will be thrown..

      • toBoolean

        public boolean toBoolean()
                  throws SBMLException
        Analog to the toDouble() method but this method tries to evaluate the value contained in this object to a boolean value. In case of numbers, one is considered true, all other values represent false.
        Returns:
        A boolean representing the value of this container. Note that if the value is an instance of CallableSBase, it can only be converted into a boolean value if the ASTNode2Compiler associated with this object compiles this value to an ASTNode2Value that contains a boolean or at least a Number value.
        Throws:
        SBMLException

      • toNumber

        public java.lang.Number toNumber()
                          throws SBMLException
        Tries to convert the value contained in this object into a double number.
        Returns:
        The number value represented by this given ASTNodeValue. In case this ASTNodeValue contains an instance of Boolean, zero is returned for false and one for true. If the value is null or cannot be converted to any number, Double.NaN will be returned. Note that if the value of this container is an instance of CallableSBase, the value can only be converted to a number if the compiler associated with this ASTNodeValue compiles this CallableSBase to an ASTNodeValue that contains a Number.
        Throws:
        SBMLException
